Here's the full pattern:

**XAML** — wrap `CollectionView` in a `RefreshView`:

```xml
<RefreshView IsRefreshing="{Binding IsRefreshing}"
             Command="{Binding RefreshCommand}">
    <CollectionView ItemsSource="{Binding Items}"
                    SelectionMode="Single"
                    SelectedItem="{Binding SelectedItem, Mode=TwoWay}"
                    SelectionChangedCommand="{Binding ItemSelectedCommand}">
        <CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
            <DataTemplate x:DataType="models:Item">
                <Grid Padding="12" ColumnDefinitions="48,*">
                    <Image Source="{Binding Icon}" WidthRequest="40" HeightRequest="40" />
                    <Label Grid.Column="1" Text="{Binding Name}" VerticalOptions="Center" />
                </Grid>
            </DataTemplate>
        </CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
        <CollectionView.EmptyView>
            <Label Text="No items found." HorizontalOptions="Center" Margin="0,20" />
        </CollectionView.EmptyView>
    </CollectionView>
</RefreshView>
```

**ViewModel** (using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm):

```csharp
public partial class ItemsViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    private readonly IApiService _api;
    private readonly INavigationService _nav;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private Item? selectedItem;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool isRefreshing;

    public ObservableCollection<Item> Items { get; } = new();

    // Pull-to-refresh: reload from API, then set IsRefreshing = false
    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task RefreshAsync()
    {
        var data = await _api.GetItemsAsync();
        MainThread.BeginInvokeOnMainThread(() =>
        {
            Items.Clear();
            foreach (var item in data)
                Items.Add(item);
        });
        IsRefreshing = false;   // hides the spinner
    }

    // Selection: navigate, then clear selection so user can re-select
    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task ItemSelectedAsync()
    {
        if (SelectedItem is null) return;

        await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"detail?id={SelectedItem.Id}");
        SelectedItem = null;    // reset so the same item can be tapped again
    }
}
```

### Key binding points

| XAML property | ViewModel member | Why |
|---|---|---|
| `ItemsSource` | `ObservableCollection<Item> Items` | Auto-updates UI on add/remove |
| `SelectedItem` (TwoWay) | `Item? SelectedItem` | Syncs tap to VM; set `null` to reset |
| `SelectionChangedCommand` | `ItemSelectedCommand` | Fires on tap → navigates to detail |
| `IsRefreshing` (TwoWay) | `bool IsRefreshing` | Controls spinner; set `false` when done |
| `Command` on RefreshView | `RefreshCommand` | Triggers API reload on pull |

### Important notes

- **Always use `ObservableCollection<T>`**, not `List<T>` — otherwise the UI won't update.
- **Set `SelectedItem = null`** after navigation so the same item can be re-selected.
- **Set `IsRefreshing = false`** at the end of your refresh command — the spinner won't stop otherwise.
- **Set `x:DataType`** on `DataTemplate` to enable compiled bindings and catch errors at build time.
- Update collections on the **UI thread** via `MainThread.BeginInvokeOnMainThread`.
